DOMAIN_SEPARATOR().details: Uses cached version if chainid is unchanged from construction.

approve(address,uint256).details: override Solmate's ERC721 approve so approve() and permit() share the _approve method The zero address indicates there is no approved address Throws error unless `msg.sender` is the current NFT owner, or an authorized operator of the current owner.

params.id: The tokenId of the NFT to approve

getPositionConfigId(uint256).details: truncates the least significant bit of the hash

returns._0: a truncated hash of the position's poolkey, tickLower, and tickUpper

getPositionLiquidity(uint256,((address,a.details: this value can be processed as an amount0 and amount1 by using the LiquidityAmounts library

params.config: the corresponding PositionConfig for the tokenId

returns.liquidity: the position's liquidity, as a liquidityAmount

returns._0: bool whether or not the position has a subscriber

modifyLiquidities(bytes,uint256).details: This is the standard entrypoint for the PositionManager

params.deadline: is the deadline for the batched actions to be executed
params.payload: is an encoding of actions, and parameters for those actions

modifyLiquiditiesWithoutUnlock(bytes,byt.details: This must be called by a contract that has already unlocked the v4 PoolManager

params.params: the parameters to provide for the actions

msgSender().details: The other context functions, _msgData and _msgValue, are not supported by this contract In many contracts this will be the address that calls the initial entry point that calls `_executeActions` `msg.sender` shouldnt be used, as this will be the v4 pool manager contract that calls `unlockCallback` If using ReentrancyLock.sol, this function can return _getLocker()

multicall(bytes[]).details: The `msg.value` should not be trusted for any method callable from multicall.

params.data: The encoded function data for each of the calls to make to this contract

returns.results: The results from each of the calls passed in via data

permit(address,((address,uint160,uint48,.details: this function is payable to allow multicall with NATIVE based actions

permit(address,uint256,uint256,uint256,b.details: payable so it can be multicalled with NATIVE related actions

params.deadline: The deadline timestamp by which the call must be mined for the approve to work
params.signature: Concatenated data from a valid secp256k1 signature from the holder, i.e. abi.encodePacked(r, s, v)
params.spender: The account that is being approved
params.tokenId: The ID of the token that is being approved for spending

permitBatch(address,((address,uint160,ui.details: this function is payable to allow multicall with NATIVE based actions

permitForAll(address,address,bool,uint25.details: payable so it can be multicalled with NATIVE related actions

params.approved: The permission to set on the operator
params.deadline: The deadline timestamp by which the call must be mined for the approve to work
params.operator: The address that will be set as an operator for the owner
params.owner: The address that is setting the operator
params.signature: Concatenated data from a valid secp256k1 signature from the holder, i.e. abi.encodePacked(r, s, v)

revokeNonce(uint256).details: Used in cases where a valid nonce has not been broadcasted onchain, and the owner wants to revoke the validity of the noncepayable so it can be multicalled with native-token related actions

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Emits the ApprovalForAll event. The contract MUST allow multiple operators per owner.Override Solmate's ERC721 setApprovalForAll so setApprovalForAll() and permit() share the _approveForAll method

params.approved: True if the operator is approved, false to revoke approval
params.operator: Address to add to the set of authorized operators

subscribe(uint256,((address,address,uint.details: Calling subscribe when a position is already subscribed will revertpayable so it can be multicalled with NATIVE related actions

params.config: the corresponding PositionConfig for the tokenId
params.data: caller-provided data that's forwarded to the subscriber contract

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: overrides solmate transferFrom in case a notification to subscribers is needed

unlockCallback(bytes).details: We force the onlyByPoolManager modifier by exposing a virtual function after the onlyByPoolManager check.

unsubscribe(uint256,((address,address,ui.details: payable so it can be multicalled with NATIVE related actionsMust always allow a user to unsubscribe. In the case of a malicious subscriber, a user can always unsubscribe safely, ensuring liquidity is always modifiable.

params.config: the corresponding PositionConfig for the tokenId
params.data: caller-provided data that's forwarded to the subscriber contract

DOMAIN_SEPARATOR().notice: Returns the domain separator for the current chain.

approve(address,uint256).notice: Change or reaffirm the approved address for an NFT

hasSubscriber(uint256).notice: Returns whether a a position should call out to notify a subscribing contract on modification or transfer

modifyLiquidities(bytes,uint256).notice: Unlocks Uniswap v4 PoolManager and batches actions for modifying liquidity

modifyLiquiditiesWithoutUnlock(bytes,byt.notice: Batches actions for modifying liquidity without unlocking v4 PoolManager

msgSender().notice: function that returns address considered executer of the actions

multicall(bytes[]).notice: Call multiple functions in the current contract and return the data from all of them if they all succeed

nonces(address,uint256).notice: mapping of nonces consumed by each address, where a nonce is a single bit on the 256-bit bitmap

permit(address,((address,uint160,uint48,.notice: allows forwarding a single permit to permit2

permit(address,uint256,uint256,uint256,b.notice: Approve of a specific token ID for spending by spender via signature

permitBatch(address,((address,uint160,ui.notice: allows forwarding batch permits to permit2

permitForAll(address,address,bool,uint25.notice: Set an operator with full permission to an owner's tokens via signature

revokeNonce(uint256).notice: Revoke a nonce by spending it, preventing it from being used again

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).notice: Enable or disable approval for a third party ("operator") to manage all of `msg.sender`'s assets

subscribe(uint256,((address,address,uint.notice: Enables the subscriber to receive notifications for a respective position

unsubscribe(uint256,((address,address,ui.notice: Removes the subscriber from receiving notifications for a respective position
